<item>
            <title>[SPARK-32516] path option is treated differently for &apos;format(&quot;parquet&quot;).load(path)&apos; vs. &apos;parquet(path)&apos;</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-32516</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When data is read, &quot;path&quot; option is treated differently depending on how dataframe is created:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
scala&amp;gt; Seq(1).toDF.write.mode(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;overwrite&quot;&lt;/span&gt;).parquet(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;/tmp/test&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)
                                                                                
scala&amp;gt; spark.read.option(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;path&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;/tmp/test&quot;&lt;/span&gt;).format(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;parquet&quot;&lt;/span&gt;).load(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;/tmp/test&quot;&lt;/span&gt;).show
+-----+
|value|
+-----+
|    1|
+-----+


scala&amp;gt; spark.read.option(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;path&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;/tmp/test&quot;&lt;/span&gt;).parquet(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;/tmp/test&quot;&lt;/span&gt;).show
+-----+
|value|
+-----+
|    1|
|    1|
+-----+
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
